<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Froontown</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <!-- [if lt IE 9] -->
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif] -->
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="navbar navbar-inverse">
        <div class="container-fluid">
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <!-- Here, we're defining the collapsed state of the navbar, and what to collapse using the "data-target=#collapsedNav" id -->
            <button type="button" class="navbar-toggle collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapsedNav">
              <span class="sr-only">Toggle Navigation</span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
              <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            </button>
            <!-- Branding stuff -->
            <a class="navbar-brand">
              <img src="app/assets/images/cutesif.jpg" style="height: 100%; width: auto;" alt="Cute SIf">
            </a>
            <p class="navbar-text"><strong>Froontown</strong></p>
          </div>

          <!-- This is the stuff that appears when on a large screen, but collapsed to mobile -->
          <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="collapsedNav">
            <ul class="nav navbar-nav">
              <li class="active"><a href="http://www.google.com">Google</a></li>
              <li class="active"><a href="http://maps.google.com">Maps</a></li>
              <li class="active"><a href="http://www.reddit.com">Reddit</a></li>

            <!-- Links and buttons below -->
              <a href="http://darksouls.wiki.fextralife.com/Dark+Souls+Wiki" class="btn btn-default navbar-btn navbar-right">Dark Souls</a>

              <li class="dropdown">
                <a href="#" class="dropdown-toggle" data-toggle="dropdown" role="button" aria-expanded="false">
                  Dropdown stuff
                  <span class="caret"></span>
                </a>
                <ul class="dropdown-menu" role="menu">
                  <li>These</li>
                  <li>Go</li>
                  <li>Nowhere</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>

      <h1>Welcome to Froontown!</h1>
      <h3> This <%= @message %> is from the controller! </h3>
      <p>This site is really busted. The nav bar up there has got a lot of placeholder.</p>
      <p>Just trying to get a basic view to appear for now.</p>
      <p>If you squish the window a bit, you'll see the navbar collapse with a burger menu. Go bootstrap!</p>

      <p> Adding some ERb for fun: </p>
      <% @count.times { %>
        <li><%= @bonus %></li>
      <% } %>
      <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
      <script src="../js/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
